The Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) Federal Operation Unit (FOU) zone ‘B’ has made seizure of various goods with Duty Paid Value (DPV) of N251,711,300 from Sokoto, Kebbi, Kano and Katsina areas. The comptroller of the FOU Zone ‘B’, Mustafa Sarkin Kebbi who made the disclosure while briefing newsmen said, the seizures were made within the past two weeks. Items seized include 50 vehicles, 1,437 bags of perboiled foreign rice, 187 bale of second hand clothing, 50 bales of blankets, 135 cartons of spaghetti, 172 kegs of PMS and 450 cartons of foreign soaps. Other items are 36 bags of sugar, 57 kegs of vegetable oil, 180 pieces of used tyres, 247 bales of textile materials, 2970 pieces of Echolac boxes, 240 parcels of Indian hemp and 600 bags of NPK 15:15:15 fertiliser. Comptroller Sarkin Kebbi also disclosed that some suspects were also arrested in respect to some of the seizures but have been given administrative bails while investigation is still ongoing. Although he said smuggling of goods such as parboiled foreign rice has reduced drastically, he however lamented that it has not been easy for his operatives with the smugglers who he said have networks of informants and have resources that could be deployed at any given time to carry out their nefarious smuggling activities. While assuring that the FOU of the zone will not relent in ensuring that activities of smugglers within the zone are brought to a stand still, he called for collaboration with the public with necessary information that will assist in the discharge of their duties.